detaileddescription.para: Suppresses snapshots that are historical, removing the metadata for lazy snapshot loading.
Note that the snapshots are not considered removed from metadata and no RemoveSnapshot changes are created.
A snapshot is historical if no ref directly references its ID.

memberdef.name: addPreviousFile

detaileddescription.para: Finds intermediate snapshots that have not been committed as the current snapshot.

Transactions can create snapshots that are never the current snapshot because several changes are combined by the transaction into one table metadata update. when each intermediate snapshot is added to table metadata, it is added to the snapshot log, assuming that it will be the current snapshot. when there are multiple snapshot updates, the log must be corrected by suppressing the intermediate snapshot entries.
A snapshot is an intermediate snapshot if it was added but is not the current snapshot.

simplesect.para: a set of snapshot ids for all added snapshots that were later replaced as the current snapshot in changes
